originalSql:
SELECT
    a.name AS actor_name,
    t.title AS movie_title,
    c.role_id AS role_id,
    ct.kind AS company_type,
    COUNT(DISTINCT m.company_id) AS company_count,
    AVG(CAST(mi.info AS INTEGER)) AS avg_movie_rating
FROM
    aka_name a
JOIN
    cast_info c ON a.person_id = c.person_id
JOIN
    aka_title t ON c.movie_id = t.id
LEFT JOIN
    movie_companies m ON t.id = m.movie_id
LEFT JOIN
    company_type ct ON m.company_type_id = ct.id
LEFT JOIN
    movie_info mi ON t.id = mi.movie_id AND mi.info_type_id = (SELECT id FROM info_type WHERE info = 'rating')
WHERE
    t.production_year BETWEEN 1990 AND 2020
GROUP BY
    a.name, t.title, c.role_id, ct.kind
HAVING
    COUNT(DISTINCT m.company_id) > 1
ORDER BY
    avg_movie_rating DESC, actor_name ASC

INNER JOIN "aka_title" ON "cast_info"."movie_id" = "aka_title"."id"
LEFT JOIN "s1" ON "aka_title"."id" = "s1"."movie_id"
LEFT JOIN "company_type" ON "s1"."company_type_id" = "company_type"."id"
LEFT JOIN "movie_info" ON "aka_title"."id" = "movie_info"."movie_id" AND "movie_info"."info_type_id" = (((SELECT "id" AS "ID"
FROM "info_type"
WHERE "info" = 'rating')))
WHERE "aka_title"."production_year" >= 1990 AND "aka_title"."production_year" <= 2020
GROUP BY "aka_name"."name", "aka_title"."title", "cast_info"."role_id", "company_type"."kind"
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT "s1"."company_id") > 1
ORDER BY 6 DESC NULLS FIRST, 1) AS "t7"

SELECT COALESCE("id", "id") AS "id", "kind"
FROM "company_type"

SELECT COALESCE("t7"."ACTOR_NAME", "t7"."ACTOR_NAME") AS "ACTOR_NAME", "t7"."MOVIE_TITLE", "t7"."ROLE_ID", "t7"."COMPANY_TYPE", "t7"."COMPANY_COUNT", "t7"."AVG_MOVIE_RATING"
FROM (SELECT MIN("aka_name"."name") AS "ACTOR_NAME", MIN("aka_title"."title") AS "MOVIE_TITLE", MIN("cast_info"."role_id") AS "ROLE_ID", MIN("s1"."kind") AS "COMPANY_TYPE", COUNT(DISTINCT "movie_companies"."company_id") AS "COMPANY_COUNT", AVG(CAST("movie_info"."info" AS INTEGER)) AS "AVG_MOVIE_RATING"
FROM "aka_name"
INNER JOIN "cast_info" ON "aka_name"."person_id" = "cast_info"."person_id"
INNER JOIN "aka_title" ON "cast_info"."movie_id" = "aka_title"."id"
LEFT JOIN "movie_companies" ON "aka_title"."id" = "movie_companies"."movie_id"
LEFT JOIN "s1" ON "movie_companies"."company_type_id" = "s1"."id"
LEFT JOIN "movie_info" ON "aka_title"."id" = "movie_info"."movie_id" AND "movie_info"."info_type_id" = (((SELECT "id" AS "ID"
FROM "info_type"
WHERE "info" = 'rating')))
WHERE "aka_title"."production_year" >= 1990 AND "aka_title"."production_year" <= 2020
GROUP BY "aka_name"."name", "aka_title"."title", "cast_info"."role_id", "s1"."kind"
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT "movie_companies"."company_id") > 1
ORDER BY 6 DESC NULLS FIRST, 1) AS "t7"

SELECT COALESCE("id", "id") AS "id", "movie_id", "info_type_id", "info", "note"
FROM "movie_info"

SELECT COALESCE("t7"."ACTOR_NAME", "t7"."ACTOR_NAME") AS "ACTOR_NAME", "t7"."MOVIE_TITLE", "t7"."ROLE_ID", "t7"."COMPANY_TYPE", "t7"."COMPANY_COUNT", "t7"."AVG_MOVIE_RATING"
FROM (SELECT MIN("aka_name"."name") AS "ACTOR_NAME", MIN("aka_title"."title") AS "MOVIE_TITLE", MIN("cast_info"."role_id") AS "ROLE_ID", MIN("company_type"."kind") AS "COMPANY_TYPE", COUNT(DISTINCT "movie_companies"."company_id") AS "COMPANY_COUNT", AVG(CAST("s1"."info" AS INTEGER)) AS "AVG_MOVIE_RATING"
FROM "aka_name"
INNER JOIN "cast_info" ON "aka_name"."person_id" = "cast_info"."person_id"
INNER JOIN "aka_title" ON "cast_info"."movie_id" = "aka_title"."id"
LEFT JOIN "movie_companies" ON "aka_title"."id" = "movie_companies"."movie_id"
LEFT JOIN "company_type" ON "movie_companies"."company_type_id" = "company_type"."id"
LEFT JOIN "s1" ON "aka_title"."id" = "s1"."movie_id" AND "s1"."info_type_id" = (((SELECT "id" AS "ID"
FROM "info_type"
WHERE "info" = 'rating')))
WHERE "aka_title"."production_year" >= 1990 AND "aka_title"."production_year" <= 2020
